Class TakePhotosActivity

java.lang.Object
  Activity
      ca.ualberta.cmput301w13t11.FoodBook.TakePhotosActivity
All Implemented Interfaces:
FView<DbManager>
public class TakePhotosActivity
extends Activity
implements FView<DbManager>

This class allows the user to take (capture) pictures and save them onto a recipe. When an SD card is not installed, BogoPicGen is called to generate 640x480 images. BogoPicGen images are stored in main memory in directory 'Pictures'

jaramill

OnSavePhoto

public void OnSavePhoto(View View)
This method saves a bitmap to the device in compressed form (.png) Depending on whether an SD card is installed, the png image is saved on the SD card or in main memory. Saving is delegated to the database. The bitmap, filepath, and unique photo id (a timestamp) are passed on to the database controller.

Parameters:
View - - The view calling this method.
